result.execSummary:
The defendant Christopher David Winchell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Christopher David Winchell is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Christopher David Winchell was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Christopher David Winchell was found guilty of Knowingly Possess Methamphetamine Waste [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.67(2)(a).
  • Christopher David Winchell was found guilty of Maintain Drug Trafficking Place [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.42(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Parties acknowledge receipt of PSI.

Atty Watterman does not object to sentence in plea agreement, gives argument for sentence credit and sets out the circumstances leading to the offenses.  Moves for expunction upon successful completion of probation.
Response by D.A. Gill.
Lynette Winchell Andrews addresses the Court.
Christopher Winchell Addresses the Court.
Court orders sentence as follows:  
Count 1:  sentence withheld, 4 yrs. probation concurrent with any other sentence - conditions set out in plea agreement, 1 yr. jail with Huber consecutive to count 3 in 16CF39, concurrent with count 2 in 16CF39
Count 2:  sentence withheld, 4 yrs. probation concurrent with any other sentence - conditions set out in plea agreement, 1 yr. jail with Huber consecutive to count 3 in 16CF39, concurrent with count 2 in 16CF39 and count 1 in 16CF59
Count 5:  sentence withheld, 4 yrs. probation concurrent with any other sentence - conditions set out in plea agreement, 9 months jail with Huber consecutive to count 3 in 16CF39, concurrent with count 2 in 16CF39 and counts 1 & 2 in 16CF59

Defendant Christopher David Winchell in court with attorney Gregg Earl Waterman.  Jenna L Gill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Defendant wishes to change plea.
Discussion re: proposed plea agreement.
Recess taken at 3:30 p.m.  -  Back in session at 3:54 p.m.
Defendant enters plea of "guilty" to Counts 1, 2 and 5.
Court questions defendant re: his plea and waiver of rights.
Parties stipulate to factual basis.
State waives right to jury trial.
Court also questions Atty Waterman re: his client's plea and waiver of rights.
Court finds plea and waiver of rights is made freely, knowingly and voluntarily.
Court accpets pleas, finds defendant guilty of Counts 1, 2 and 5.
Court orders PSI - file by 7/6/17.
Set for sentencing 7/18/17 at 3:00 p.m. (1-1/2 hrs.)
Probation agent shall be present.
Counts 3 and 4 are dismissed.
